post_text: Inkster Preparatory Academy’s (IPA) is PROUD of the growth of our students! Our students demonstrated the highest amount of growth of all CMU-authorized charter public schools in 2018-29 on the NWEA MAP Assessment in reading. With a Median Growth Percentile (MGP) of 72, students on average grew significantly more than their like peers nationwide. A typical student demonstrates a growth percentile of 50, which is generally considered a year’s worth of academic gains. In math, IPA’s students demonstrated an MGP of 74, which was the second-highest of all CMU-authorized charter public schools. inksterprep.org

post_text:
Inkster Preparatory Academy Summer Enrichment Wrap Up

Inkster Preparatory Academy has wrapped up its 2019 Summer Enrichment Program. Students, in grades Pre K through 5th were able to bolster their math, reading, writing and technical skills over a four week period. Our Summer Enrichment Staff-created fun and engaging activities for the more than 25 students in attendance in an effort to prevent summer loss and possibly increase student academic achievement. Also, Inkster Preparatory Academy would like to shout out, “The Meet Up and Eat Up” program for providing lunches to our students throughout the Summer Enrichment Program!

post_text:
2019 Summer Carnival Success at Inkster Preparatory

Inkster Preparatory Academy has done it again. On Saturday, July 27th starting at 11:00 am, Inkster Preparatory Academy hosted its third annual Carnival Event for the Inkster Community and Inkster Prep families. The Carnival was well attended with Bouncy Houses, games, snow cones, cotton candy, hotdogs and more free to all that came out. New parents had a chance to enroll their students, meet the Principal and/or take a tour of the school if desired. Families already a part of Inkster Preparatory Academy were able to meet with friends and staff for a few hours of community fun! Families still interested in enrolling their children may do so during Inkster Preparatory Academies summer hours: Monday – Friday (9:00 am – 4:00 pm).

post_text:
The Mayor of Inkster visited Inkster Preparatory Academy!

We were excited to have the mayor of Inkster, Mayor Nolan, visit our school for Inkster Prep’s first “Stomp the Mayor” contest. Students from Inkster Prep asked the Mayor questions about Black History designed to “stump” him. Some of our top students asked the mayor some pretty tough questions about famous Black people from Inkster, MI. Despite tough questioning, Mayor Nolan remained victorious and was able to answer most of the questions successfully. Finally, our students took part in a learning session by Councilwoman Watley and learned a lot about past and present African American achievers! Our students are excited and look forward to next year’s “Stump the Mayor”.

December 8, 2018 at 12:36 PM ·

Zeta Phi Beta Sorority making difference at Inkster Preparatory Academy!!!! ALL ZETA'S PLEASE COMMENT

Every school across the world know how important literacy is for our students. What greater way to encourage students to read then to wonderful and engaging school library. Our partners, Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Inc. Zeta Nu Zeta Chapter donated their time, energy, and resources into helping to transform our room full of book into a place where the students can have a real library experience. We would like to thank them for their kind efforts and dedication to making our school and this world a better place.

I AM ASKING ALL OF THE ZETA'S TO PLEASE SHARE, COMMENT, OR LIKE THIS POST. I want the world to know about the work that you are doing at Inkster Prep Academy.

post_text:
Fatherhood at my School:

This is one of my proudest post! I have a lot of fathers that are really involved in their child’s life and active at my school. I decided to make a fatherhood board in the hallway of my school that shows how active and engaged my fathers are in their child’s life. I have so many fathers who are picking and dropping of their child and volunteering throughout the school day. I am so proud of all of my committed dads! This is the most I have ever seen in 16 years of education. #fatherhood #education

Inkster Prep Celebrates Kindergarten Promotion
Family, parents and friends showed up in style to celebrate the promotion of their kindergartens to the first grade. More than 200 guest were present and a good time was had by all. Our new first graders brought the house down with their special performances and cheery smiles while teachers had tearful words and a beautiful slide show to show parents what their students have been learning all year!

post_text:
We’re still flying high with aerodynamic lessons at IPA.

Our second grade class enjoyed the spring weather and made airplanes. They used what they know about airplane models to create airplanes and measure the distances that their airplanes could travel. Having hands on, STEM type lessons are just a few small ways in which IPA uses out of the box strategies to keep our kids engaged and learning in a rigorous way.

Hello Inkster Prep Families,

Inkster Preparatory Academy will be closed for Friday, February 9, 2018. We are making this decision now based on the consistent predictions of a significant weather event anticipated in southeast Michigan throughout the day and tomorrow.

We understand that in situations like this, our families benefit from timely notice in order to make arrangements and keep our students, staff and families safe.

Mr. Shawn Hurt, Principal
